# Quick Look at the Data

The starter dataset contains **30,000 webpages**. Approximately **54%** of the pages are labeled as declining based on their recent traffic trend. The average number of impressions over the last 90 days is **XXX**, and the average CTR is **XXX**. These statistics show that the dataset contains a diverse range of webpages with varying levels of visibility and performance, making it suitable for building a prioritization model.

# Careful Words

This project does not prove that refreshing a webpage will increase its traffic or improve search rankings. Instead, it identifies pages that appear to have characteristics associated with declining performance based on historical search and engagement signals. The ranked recommendations are intended to support human decision-making and should be reviewed before any content changes are made.

